content: Hello everybody! It is time to begin our lesson
glad to see many of you here.
I hope you all enjoyed the photos about the Team World Championship in our Forum.
Later there will be more, even some videos perhaps.
Today, we will study an important game from Team WC.
in the match Estonia - Russia-1, the game became very important between Sushkov and me.
If we could beat Russia 3:1, it would be a big chance for us, to hope for the 1st place.
Timo quickly got a good position against Nikonov at the 4th table.
It seemed that Timo could soon win,
but he was perhaps too much afraid of famous Nikonov,
so he did not try to attack.
Sushkov had set i8 against me.
And after change of color he played this 4th move.
It was hard choice for me.
Black, as you know, can choose two ways:
to go to standard variant of i8 opening, with move 5-g8,
or to transfer to d11 opening with 5-h6.
I looked at my left, Tunnet and Ants were both facing d11 in their games.
but 5-g8 no win as i know, nowdays
if I go to d11 as black,
Russia team's interest is to keep balanced score.
while we must make effort to win,
because we were some points behind them at that moment.
I realized, if I choose d11 opening,
it will be not good for our team,
on the other hand, I know there are difficulties in i8 standard variant too.
after 30 minutes, I placed the 5th moves.
Tunnet and Klimashin played so fast next to me.
This time Tunnet hurried too much,
and he got into a losing trap as white.
Luckily, Ants beat Sinyov on 3rd table soon.
Tunnet lost, and then it was up to Timo and me, to do something.
if Timo and I both win,
we get 3:1, and all is possible.
does anyone of you know this pattern?
before the match, we had instructed Timo, to play safely, not to lose on 4th table,
he did his task too well.
its a pity, he could easily win there.
first, he could play g12 here,
but he played here, still ok.
etc, he kept filling up the board as black
i forgot the pattern on lower side
but win-move is waiting for black
obvious and safe time to play and win
who wants to show black win, say me
just a try, not very sure
I think with the help of right side materials,it will be easier for black, that's the idea of 37.
it also seems, black has VCT here.
I don't find yet, but Iwill try.
I dont know if Timo would have found win here or not,
but I think at least he should have tried with 33-d11
While Timo and Nikonov's game seemed to be unclear, Sushkov was very concerned about that game.

he often looked at Nikonov's moves,
and worried that Timo might win.
our game developed by normal path.
This variant is not so popular nowadays,
because black can often force the draw here even if black fails to win,
so for white, wanting to win, the variant is not good.
However, for Sushkov, the task was given to keep at least half point.
in order to keep match balanced,
furthermore, he hoped to suprise me in this variant.
How many of you know about this 28th move?
let you try your ideas for black before we continue watching game
others meanwhile, try to think along
imagine as if you were black
So, the way Sushkov played was not a gamble,
Yes, they analysed a lot before match,
yes, other 28 have been all black wins, as far as I have seen in games.
In fact, I almost forgot about those.
but idea was something like this:
and somehow connecting left and right forces
Here, I spent over 1 hour to think next move.
but it is a bad move.
seems like nice way to win
and black cannot reach to k6
I thought for a long time about the variant we just tried,
but Russians had analysed a lot about itm
and if I play all this,
it will be too hard to make a draw later,
because now the whole left wing is under white's control,
and even right win may surprise
after 1 hour of thinking, I decided to play a new move,
to surprise him a bit too.
in the game, i faced many difficult questions here.
i wanted to make some active space move,
but i was worried about counter-attack.
I regret I did not have previous home analysis about it,
first: win or draw is a question
therefore I had to spend much time in game,
to invent new plans for black
it was the only way to catch Russia-1
i so much wanted to play here.
but then i became worried of counter-attack
therefore, I had to find some idea,
which is active enough to prevent counter-attacks,
My trouble was, i had spent too much time on moves 5 and 29,
i believe, black has a potential here,
to be successful after long home research.
but in game situation, i had to make decision fast.
I decided to play three first, to avoid counter.
and I did not like it. :(
but I could not think of better plan in that moment.
it was clear to both players:
the left side space will be the key of the game.
therefore, my moves 33 and 35 carried hope, to conquer for left side.
he saw this attempt of course,
and he decided to cut me off,
the best method to cut blacks from stretching towards left.
the connection through j2 gives black a threat.
very big pressure on both players here.
he puzzled about several ideas and tactics.
he wanted to play something very sharp, in the are of e8 or so,
but it seems black is too dangerous
and when he looked at Nikonov's game (still going on),
he saw Nikonov in trouble there,
and decided, the risk at this point may bring 1:3 disaster to Russia,
so he had to find safest possible plan here.
he used the four, wise move.
else, I was planning to take j6 myself.
now, black has right side win
and same time, black eliminated 38_42 line
so black can play better on left later.
it cuts all my win hopes
I thought very hard here, but time was soon over,
as you know, there was no bayomi clock.

"Russia-1 vs Estonia, my game with Sushkov lasted very long. I spent 149 minutes for the first 40 moves, and then I had only 1 minute left. I had to fill the whole board until there is no chance for 5-in-a-row to get the draw. In the moment of the photo, I have 25 seconds left, but most of the board is full already. The draw came soon."
so i played very fast from there.
sure, he had all the advantages of time,
but, somehow he had weakened his own position,
there is also a special draw rule?
he was too much possessed by my time shortage,
yes, draw is fixed when no chance for 5 on board.
so i had to play enough moves in 1 minute, to fill the board.
had he planned to win by time? :)
the crowd was watching the ending.
to gain win, by help of time pressure.
you play the move the press the clock? So how can you play that fast :))
if he took longer time to think would it better for him?
however, by move 61, my situation became good.
he had too much time on his clock,
the player has to record every move on protocol,
as long as he has over 5 minutes left.
so, he was recording every move,
giving me time to get another stone,
he should wait for his clock to become 5 and then go
but then, there is another danger:
with move 61, black became very strong all of the sudden.
if he had wasted all his time before that,
then he might be in time trouble as well,
because he needed quite some time here,
to defend against my upper attack.
and here, he nearly made a mistake.
he was about to place the stone to m11,
but he stopped himself in last moment
he spent much time, finding the only defense finally.
i had played this move earlier
so he's lucky not wasting all his time
if I had not played a four here
without n8, black can win with m5
but i had so little time.
i knew i could spend 1/3 of the second on each move.
and then no win, because of 3x3
this is how it went on,
the clock was on right side of the board,
its more trouble to play fast
if I had been on his seat,
you can see the photo in Forum,
so trouble for both players. Exchanging seats will benefit both of you
the hands of both players move so fast,
when i had about 25 seconds left,
by placing the stone on edge
it was impossible to recover the record of the game,
so officially, on protocol it states draw on move 93
i was surprised he offered draw so soon.
because, he nearly had as much time left as I did
Sushkov, if you keep playing in this speed,
you will lose by time before i reach to my 20th second
it was the joke after draw of course
yes, very tired game, but exciting.
same time, the game Timo - Nikonov had already ended as draw.
practically, losing hope to get the 1st place.
but it is not possible to make analyses during 60 seconds
and still manage to fill the board in time
the chance for win was small, in my opinion,
and we needed half point more than big loss risk
so, any spent second on thinking there could cost me the game.
I think so,draw is good result foe B
thank you all, i hope you enjoyed it.
